SSH (22) – Windows does not enable this by default.

Telnet (23) – Typically found on legacy Unix/Linux.

rpcbind (111), nfs (2049) – Native to Unix/Linux for remote file sharing.

exec (512), login (513), shell (514) – Classic Unix remote commands (r-services).

X11 (6000) – The X Window System, used on Linux/Unix desktops.

MySQL (3306), PostgreSQL (5432) – Open-source databases, common on Linux servers.

IRC (6667) – Often runs on Linux; not typical on Windows.
